  "description": "A SaaS-classic hero pairing a tight content column with a product screenshot mounted in the device frame of your choice — browser window, macbook lid, phone, or tablet. Built for software products whose conversion lever is showing the actual UI.",
  "descriptions": {
    "descriptive": "A 5/7 split with the headline column on the left (eyebrow status pill, optional highlighted word in the headline, subheadline, primary + secondary CTAs, optional trust badges) and the product screenshot on the right wrapped in a chosen device chrome. Browser frame includes a fake address bar; macbook frame mimics a laptop lid; phone and tablet frames render rounded device shells. A soft primary-color glow sits behind the device for depth.",
    "usage": "Use as the homepage opener for SaaS, mobile apps, productivity tools, and any product whose interface is its strongest argument. Choose the device frame that matches where the user lives: browser for B2B web apps, phone for consumer mobile, macbook for design tools, tablet for enterprise field tools.",
    "audienceFit": "Reads as credible to founders, product leaders, and buyers who have seen this pattern done well by Linear, Vercel, and Notion. Avoid for brands selling experience-led products (hospitality, fashion, restaurants) where a screenshot sells nothing."
  }
